In a small #pot, combine @Jasmine Rice{½%cup}, 3⁄4 cup water (1 1⁄2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Place sealed honey packets in a #small bowl with enough hot water to cover. (Warming the honey helps make it pourable.) Halve @Mandarin Orange{1}; squeeze juice from both halves over a separate #small bowl. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Halve, core, and thinly slice @Long Green Pepper{1} into strips.

To bowl with mandarin juice, whisk in @Honey{2%teaspoon}, @Ketchup{1}, and @Soy Sauce{2%tablespoon} until combined.

Open package of @Diced Skinless Dark Meat Chicken{20%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid. In a #medium bowl, combine chicken, @Cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, a pinch of salt, and @Pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan over medium-high heat. Add coated chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, ~{3%minutes}. Add scallion whites and green pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is cooked through and a crust forms, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Stir in honey mandarin sauce and continue to cook until sauce has thickened and everything is thoroughly coated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @Butter{½%TBSP} (1 TBSP for 4 servings). Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Once rice is done, stir in @Butter{½%TBSP} (1 TBSP for 4 servings); fluff with a #fork.

Divide rice and chicken stir-fry between shallow #bowls in separate sections. Top everything with @Sliced Almonds{½%ounce}, scallion greens, and as much @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} as you like. Serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.